<br>
<br>
Many, Many wizards still have to pay 20k for Sunstrike and almost all wizards will never see EER or Garrisons. You think its not a problem for Mages to be out nuking us by 400 damage at 61 with a spell bought off a vendor? Pullease. Wizards dont have pets. All we do is nuke. Our nukes should always under every circumstance be better than anyone elses. The problem with Talon isnt that mages have it, it isnt even really that its lvl 61. The problem is that it is off a vendor. Wizards are continuously held to different standards when it comes to getting our nukes and this must absolutly stop. I have always been an advocate of fairness on these boards and it is extremely frustrating to see this spell on a vendor. <br>
<br>
I was in a group the other night with a mage who had much less AA than me doing WAY more damage. This person had SCF3 and was critting for 3800s. I didnt have focus and with sunstrike would crit for 3230. It was so ridiculous that melee started talking about it in groupchat. They knew I had better gear, more AAs, and were very puzzled by this. I recieved 3 tells about it. When you start recieving tells from melee because its clear you are being outnuked by a lesser nuke class, there is a friggen problem.<br>
<br>
Dont get me wrong, I love mages, I really do. I dont want them nerfed and I dont really know what the solution is, but Talon off a vendor is absolutly overpowered in its current form. Once again I will tell this story: This happened before long ago. Runes for IC only dropped off Vox/Naggy and mages could buy Lava bolt off a vendor. It was ridiculous. The fix was that VI put Rend into the game to equalize. This situation is no different. It really does a disservice to gloss over the power of Talon. Everyone knows how easy it is to land a bolt in an XP group, We as Wizards had to learn this. The difficulty in landing a bolt is greatly overexaggerated. Seriously, we KNOW better, so its kinda insulting to our intelligence to keep hearing this inacurate argument.<br>
<br>
To Recap: 95% of Wizards Still cannot get EER or Garrisons, many Still are forced to pay 20k+pp for Sunstrike, while mages can outnuke us with a spell off a vendor. This just isnt right. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oxoxoxoxox>Oxoxo Xoxox</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalRainbow.gif" BORDER=0> at: 10/31/02 9:46:09 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faithkills>Faithkills</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1229<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/31/02 12:21:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Talon on a vendor. Not cool(Serious discussion only)</span><hr size=1> Has anyone checked if FoT is Wizard useable now?<br>
