Pets do have place in the conversation for the simple fact that they are the primary difference between mages and wizards.  Mages get their damage from pets, damage shields, and nukes.  Wizards get their damage from nukes.  Given that both classes are offensive based, Wizard nukes &gt; Mage nukes _because_ mages have alternative forms of damage.<br>
<br>
Essentially, wizards should have better nukes because mages have pets.  The only debate that I've seen is whether or not FoT IS better or inappropriately close to the average wizard's nukes.  Many mages will tell you no, some wizards will tell you no.  Most mages are using in quite a bit in game though, and seem pretty happy with it.<br>
<br>
My personal opinion is that it given the difficulty of aquiring level 60 luclin nukes there is an issue here.  I personally don't like the idea of just giving wizards the bolt, for a couple of reasons.  First I think wizards should be better at nuking in all situations.  Second I think that FoT is a nice unique spells to mages, and that it would be cheating them out of some of their uniqueness to give it to us.  <br>
<br>
